	   <tr><td colspan=2>It's very simple to do and a lot of fun to do it.<br><br>levels 1-4 bats and skellies outside Kaladim, boring but it works<br><br>levels 5-9 the skellies at the druid ring. Might have to group but if you've never played a cleric you'd better start learning what you mean to a tank.<br><br>levels 9-13 dervs...They are always camped but they give great xp and a healer is always welcome. Turn the rings in to the orc in SRO for some crappy money and faction w/ temple of life. You'll need it.<br><br>levels 14-17 orcs in oasis, since you've got heal at level 14 tanks will start to love you. The orcs drop good money and money is a clerics best friend<br><br>levels 17-22 The aviak guards in Lake Rathe, again they're always camped but I never had trouble finding a group. people love clerics<br><br>levels 22-30 Lake of Ill omen and after level 24 you can start killing giants in Frontier Mountains. the Lake is faster xp but FM has much better loot for your level. And again, clerics are always broke.<br><br>That's a step by step guide to leveling. I'd suggest spending levels 18 and 19 in unrest. It's a great place to build technique and become more accustomed to your role in the group.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
