	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96663486929138><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=96663486929138>Weapon choice</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=96663486929138#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=649><span id= >Phidget</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>2 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 5:41 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There are 3 stages in most clerics lives involving what they equip as their primary weapon.&nbsp;&nbsp;At low levels, a 2 hand blunt will let you deal 20ish pts of damage per swing, killing many 1-10 mobs in just a few swings.  This will let you level faster at these low levels, but is not a good overall choice for later.  <br>   After the first few levels(1-10ish) it is time to start using one hand blunt.  The reason for this is not damage dealt per swing, but amount of stat bonuses per item held.  Example: 1 hand weapon and a shield together can give you 10/30 attack speed, but also together they add +17wisdom(which is more mana)10 ac, and a few other smaller stat modifiers.  Now a 2hand blunt weapon will give you an attack of 16/40, but with only 5 wisdom, NO ac, and little other stat increases.  Considering how ineffective at melee clerics are, it is pointless to waste 2 slots on one item as you move up in levels.  <br>   At very high levels most clerics give up ALL weapons because there are non-weapon items that add better stat increases and mana than weapon choices.  Occasionally we pull out the old "beat down stick" just to have some fun, but it is at the cost of what we need most, "mana and ac."<br>    So with this in mind young clerics, I don't recommend saving money up for that expensive bashing 2 hander, instead save the cash for a good one hand weapon and shield, and do what we do best  "Keep folks Alive"<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
