	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 2:59 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The capability to stun is one of the cleric's best tools in the game.<br><br>We get our first stun very early on.&nbsp;&nbsp;It does no damage, but will stun the target for up to 12 seconds or so.<br><br>It can be a lifesaver even at low levels.<br><br>Those pesky casting orcs and madmen?  With well-timed stuns you and/or your group will take very little spell damage.<br><br>The next stun, Holy Might, does up to 60 points of damage.  This is another extremely useful stun.  Because it costs very little mana, but packs a nice punch, it makes a perfect addition while fighting casters, but also to take out a running mob, or stop it long enough for tanks or other casters to kill it.<br>Care must be taken when grouping with bards or enchanters who use mesmerize spells because the damage from Holy Might will break mez.  Stun will not.<br><br>Each additional stun spell clerics get do more damage.  Mana efficiency can be tripled if you use stuns with care - 2 or 3 memmed at one time is perfect for a group fighting casting mobs.  Especially wizard/enchanter type mobs (i.e., the evil eyes in Beholder, any shaman or wizard mob, etc.).  Timing the stuns is the key - work with it a bit in a full group to get it down.<br><br>Especially in groups with enchanters, or pure casters who overnuke, stun can be a real lifesaver.  I frequently use it to assist the enchanter during big pulls.  The key is to stun the target of the mez before it's mezzed, if possible.  Basically, the enchanter needs time to mez the critter, and they can't do it if they're getting the tar kicked out of them.<br><br>To sum it up - <br>Stuns are perfect for casting mobs (keep in mind that giants and dragons, as well as some wurms, are not stunnable).  It keeps them from casting and saves a great deal of mana.<br>Stuns work well on running creatures, giving your group a chance to finish them off without root or snare.<br>Stuns can be an enchanter's best friend - but only Stun - the other DD/stun spells will break a mez.  Watch them carefully when casting, and duck to interrupt casting if mez takes while you're casting.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>--Salina<br>Erudite Vicar</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
