	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes stuns are a godsend&nbsp;&nbsp;and a cleric that knows how to use them correctly becomes a well "in demand" cleric as word spreads quickly of how good you are.   A couple things though,  the lvl 1 stun does not stun for 12 secs...maybe 3 secs,  but it is less then the duration of any of the other stuns.  <br>The best way to time your stuns to do a permanent stun is to cast your lvl 1 one  then wait a second  then your medium lvl one  then wait a second then the first one will be back  recast the first one then wait a sec then vcast the lvl 34 one (force i think it was called)  then rinse and repeat.<br><br>this technique is especially usefull in dueling situations as a good cleric can usually defeat most wizards of equal to a few lvls higher without losing much mana....stun then nuke then stun  beating on them the whole time.  and always save enough so that if you must revert to melee to finish them off you can heal up those last couple nukes they may have the mana for (but usually  they are about as low mana as you)<br><br>Suren D`Arcaanin<br>Faustt D`Arcaanin<br>Chemosh D`Arcaanin<br>Georthe Silvanus<br>Gunthaar Trueblade<br><br>Cazic Thule Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
