	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9666204597880><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=9666204597880>Creating your cleric: Race</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=9666204597880#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=607><span id=Sage>Gedran</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>99 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 1:40 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.16]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Of all the races of Norrath, only 7 can be clerics.&nbsp;&nbsp;Dark elves, High elves, Humans, Dwarves, Gnomes, Erudites, and Halflings.  Each type, has there own racial abilities that add to how well the cleric can be played.  DE's have ultravision as well as hide which can be useful.  High elves have the highest wisdom for more mana, as well as infravision, making them my favorite for this class.  Humans are blind as bats but they do get an exp bonus making it easier to level.  Dwarves are probably the other best class for clerics, while they don't have as much wisdom, they make up for it in str and stamina.  Gnomes, like Dwarves, have infravison, but not too much wisdom, they make up for it in dex and agi, but those don't really come in handy.  Erudites have the second most wisdom, but like Humans, they can't see at all.  Halflings also come with the ability to hide and have infravision.<br>If you are making an evil cleric, probably you would want to pick a DE, gnomes don't really get much guild support, and most of their special quests come from Neriak anyway.  <br>Of the lighter races, High elves and Dwarves make the best clerics.  They have nice starting areas, and many quests availible to them.  They are also in a well populated area which gives them an advantage of saftey, and people to group with.<br>Erudites, aren't all that bad, with the exception of their night vision, and the completely horrid starting area.  If you are going to make an Erudite cleric, head over to Antonica from day 1 or you will have a tough time leveling.<br>Humans and gnomes, are the runts.  Halflings are slightly better, and they all have a few good bonuses, but are pretty much inferior to the other choices.<br>Gedran<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
