	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK, a couple of notes to add to Gedram's quality post.&nbsp;&nbsp;As an Erudite cleric your starting area is pretty crappy, IF you are good.  If you worship Cazic-Thule and start in Paineel your starting area is actually pretty nice.  You can level here from 1-5 very quickly, with no zoning, very little risk, and almost no competetion for kills(this place is empty).  Another thing is if you start here I would recommend NOT doing any of the newbie quests.  Some of them are pretty good for low levs, but they all lower faction with the good erudites and this could give you a prob travelling through erudin(which you'll have to do).  By the way if you run through Erudin to the docks and avoid the mage guild you should be OK.<br><br>Another thing about blindness.  Human and Erudite clerics have available to them an item called a Fright Forged Helm.  It gives Deadeye(infravision and see invis) along with some nice stats( AC 11 +2str +4wis -5 char).  However it is a no-drop quest item that requires killing 2 tough rare spawns.  You probly need to be high 30's solo or 30 with a group, but the spawns are pretty rare so getting a group to wait around might be tough unless your in a guild or can bribe them.  Dont expect to get this item anytime soon, but it is a possibility and may be worth the wait and effort to be able to see.  Also note that the quest comes from Paineel, so it is no prob for evil erudites and possibly evil human clerics.  But others will probly have big faction probs.  Maybe an enchanter or bard could help you out, or maybe a wolf-form would, Im not sure.  Good Luck.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
