	   <a name=9666199506605></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9666199506605><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=9666199506605>Creating your Cleric: Stats</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=9666199506605#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=607><span id=Sage>Gedran</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>99 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 1:32 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Be VERY careful about the race and base stats of your cleric, they will be unchangeable, and very important later on.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Strength: With my cleric, I made the mistake of not giving him enough strength.  OUCH, Clerics can wear the best armor of all the casters, unfortunately, this usually means a lot of weight.  In addition, it gives you extra power to carry loot without becoming encumbered, as well as giving more damage after lvl 20.<br>Stamina: While not important as some of the other skills, stamina partialy determines your HP's, and it also determines how long you can stay underwater, swing your blunt weapons, and jump.  It's really up to you what you want to do here.<br>Agility:  This really isn't a necessary stat for clerics.  It's good to have to help avoid hits, and it must be kept above 75 to have no AC penalty, and have more agi when you get encumbered, but don't put to many stat points into it.<br>Dexterity:  This still isn't very useful to clerics, with the exception of determining if your spells get interrupeted when your hit.(just read below that this probably is not true) So even more than before, this isn't a useful place to use up skill points.<br>Wisdom: *divine noises* This is THE MOST IMPORTANT stat for a cleric, without wisdom you have no mana, without mana you can't heal, and without heals, you might as well have been a warrior.  This determines your mana amount, plus, since this stat should be higher than your intelligence, it determines how fast you learn skills.<br>Intelligence: Amazingly, this stat isn't really all that usefull to a cleric.  In most people, it determines how fast you learn a skill, but when your Wisdom is higher it does not.  Probably, you don't want to waste your points here either.<br>Charisma: A little charisma boost never hurts, it is known to get you better prices, and is also rumored to make your buff's last longer (I can't confirm this, and I am doubting the validity of that possiblity)  It's up to you if you want to put points here.<br>Gedran<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
