<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=9668878856873></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9668878856873><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=9668878856873>RE: Creating your Cleric: Stats</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=9668878856873#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 21st 3:58 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A few corrections:<br><br>1. Stamina- Basically accurate.&nbsp;&nbsp;Having a high stamina is a minor help at best.  I can't think of any races that actually want to invest any starting points in it.<br><br>2. Agility- ALWAYS ALWAYS ALWAYS have this stat at 75 or above.  If you don't you will take a substantial penalty on your armor class.  Anything above 75 adds to your AC, but in much smaller amounts.<br><br>3. Dexterity has precisely ZERO use for clerics.  Getting spells interrupted has nothing to do with your dexterity.  This was a common myth (perpetuated by the original instruction book of all things) that has since been debunked.  Also helps for weapon procs, but the difference is so small that any points put here are pretty much wasted.<br><br>4. Wisdom- agree on this big-time.  Max it out.<br><br>5. Good call on intelligence.  Never worth any extra points.<br><br>6.  Charisma- ZERO effect on buff length.  Not bad for buying/selling, but I would put points elsewhere.<br><br>IMO, you always wanna put 25 out of 30 points into Wisdom at the start, and your other 5 points where they would be needed most.  That means:<br><br>Dwarves: +5 to agility (this is VERY important)<br><br>All others: +5 to strength<br><br>This is definitely not hard and fast, and you won't be permanently screwed if you allocated points differently- it would just make your life a bit easier.  when i started my halfling cleric, the dexterity-for-interruption myth was still commonly accepeted, so I put 5 points into dex instead of strength.  The extra 5 points of strength would have been nice over my career, but it hasn't really hurt me all that much.<br><br>Puggins Fizzlefoot<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
