	   <a name=96661940917224></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96661940917224><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=96661940917224>PvP Class Strategy: Necro</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=96661940917224#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=607><span id=Sage>Gedran</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>99 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 1:23 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Cleric Vs. Necro:&nbsp;&nbsp;The necro is probably the most opposite class casting wise to the cleric, therefore, most cleric spells are directly related to destroying the necro.  If you know that you will be involved in a PvP battle with a necro, try to cast your HP/AC (courage, center, etc), AC (holy armor, spirit armor) buffs which should be on anyway, as well as, resist disease, poison, fire, and, if you have it, magic.  These will give you extra resistance against the types of spells Necro's can cast.  The main danger once you get in the battle is the Necro himself( once the Necro dies his pet kills itself), not the pet.  If you must attack the pet, try rooting it, or casting a fear undead type spell, to get it off of you and take on the necro.  Casting Flash of light, which can knock out his spell casting ability, then try to get close to melee range, since you can wear better armor and interrupt his spells.  Cast a sucession of stuns, and recast of flash of light, as well as you DD If you MUST.  If you have to fight the necro pet, make sure you have Ward or Expulse Undead line of spells ready, since these, will drain Necro pet life very quickly.  Always remember to watch your mana bar and if it starts getting low, target yourself very quickly, cast a heal, and retarget your enemy.  Also remember, getting your spells off is very important, always try casting RIGHT after you are hit, or right after you stun.<br>If you have to run, know that if your health is into the last bar, you will have lost stamina and not run very fast, and always have your Divine aura memmed for that helpful 18secs of Invincibility!<br>Gedran<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
