	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 21st 3:37 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmmmm, <br><br>One wonders just how much practical PvP expertise you have.&nbsp;&nbsp;Perhaps you mean duels, of which I have little expertise, rather than the open warfare of the Zeks of which I have ample practice (both as a cleric and necro).  Of course, your advice to have basic buffs is sound.  The resistances are nice, but many people don't seem to find time to cast them, perhaps they should find the time to have them up 100% of the time.  One important buff you left out was resist fire for the heat blood series.<br><br>As for the pet vs the necro:  a good necro will let the pet get in the first hit so you don't get the necro auto targeted.  By the time you get the pet rooted, which is a good way to deal with the pet, and begin to deal with the necro, you may well have a number of DOTs on you and you will find your movement impared.  Sure, you want to engage, melee and kill the necro, you just can't.  That pet isn't going away, it is mearly parked for a while.  Everytime the pet brakes the root, you get a new set of DOTS and a few whacks from the pet.  Time is on the necro's side.  He isn't going to stand around and go toe to toe with you, he is going to kite you like any other MOB he fights solo.  If you elect to stay around and try to win, you will die most of the time and the necro will run away the rest of the time.  Only a very green, very unlucky or very stupid necro will be beaten to death.  Of course, you can always hope that a guard or other MOB will get involved and kill the necro and/or his pet for you.<br><br>Flash of light is a great way to disrupt the necro.  However, call me a coward, but if I get the pet rooted and the necro blinded I am running or gating.  The wonderful thing about a cleric and PvP is that you are really hard to kill.  A cleric isn't good at killing other people unless he starts with a big advantage.<br><br>There are many times when you are already dead long before you realize it.  DOTs are mean that way.  Even if the pet is dead or missing, you are going to have a hard time killing the necro.  After all, he has lots of ways to run away.  (Shadow step, gate, gather shadows, darkness etc.)  <br><br>Divine aura is a lot less effective vs a necro than almost any other opponet.  When you are at 1 bubble, the DOTs on you alone might be enough to kill you.  Divine aura is not going to help with that.   Plus, Divine Aura lasts 18 seconds not 30.<br><br>Wisdom above all,<br><br>  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
