	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 21st 4:04 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I Play a Cleric on a pvp server and I would say most of this is pretty good.&nbsp;&nbsp;You are right that a cleric  just cant deal the damage to kill somone most of the time but you can survive forever.<br><br>  Fire resist is a Must for Ignite bones at higher levels.<br><br>  What I find works much better for the pet is to either used dread of night, panic the dead, or Simply blind the pet and step back.  It will give you additional time while the pet runs back to you or got too far out of range and cant find its ways back.  <br><br>If you can get the necro blinded it is often a good idea to use DA or DB then as hopefully  if they have spell hotkeyed (which everyone should) they will then preceed to cast those dots on you while you are invulerable and not see that they are not affecting you.  Just watch out a good player will notice the buffing sound of the da and count out those 18 seconds.  <br><br>Your stuns are great too with 4 stuns at level 50 if you can get them to stick you can stop the necro from casting any spell and kill them without a problem.  It gets hard when they start draining life back.  Remember that necros now have that scream stun spell which can give them the time to cast 1 dd or dot if you dont resist it.<br><br>The other way to go would be to simply play purley defensively.  Put up your cure disease poison, nulify magic and a fast casting heal. and remove or heal anything they throw at you  try to keep them stuned out of casting the drains.  If they use 300 mana for a Eblot and you cure it with 90 mana taking less then 100 dmg they will tend to run out of mana.  Unerfed pumice are very good here too as well as antipoison potion from shaman and disease or from the spider in Kaesora. As they get lower on mana they will be in skeleform and drain their life for mana if they get confident that they dont need to worry about damage they may let it get low this is when you can pull out a retrobution and take the kill.  Becarefull if they run off as they are doing this though becaseu they can drain life back from the wildlife.  <br><br>If they run away if you plan on continuting the battle either dont let them run to refill their mana or take the time to med heal and rebuff if playing defensivly.  I once had a battle with an even con necro at 43 last 2 rl hours because i was playing defensive, my only problem is at 43 Wrath was not cutting it for the end dd and the necro resisted the stun and got out of range before I could finish her.  <br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
