	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96661871529134><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=96661871529134>Player vs. Player: Casting</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=96661871529134#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 1:11 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>On a PK server such as Vallon, Tallon, or Rallos Zek, cleric spells can be a great advantage to a single pk, or a group of pk'ers.&nbsp;&nbsp;First of all, the low lvl spell, flash of light, is one of the most useful spells both on casters, and warrior, since it blocks the player from being able to see where to go, or, unless hotkeyed, cast any spells.  The other useful spell line, is the stun spells, these can both interrupt players, and keep them inactive for a few seconds as well as, at later levels, do some DD damage.  Root can be useful in stopping people from turning and running as well.  Direct damage is not a cleric specialty unless fighting undead, such as a necro pet.  Buffs are also use full in pre battle Player vs Player fights, and will sometimes keep you from dying.<br>Gedran<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
