	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 25th 7:35 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As you get into the range of the wonderful Atone spell, you learn to use this more and more, espcialy after casting a full heal (nothing like agroing the froglok ghoul lord). Just remember, we have spells that draw mobs, and you are going to have to deal with them in ways other than Div aura (it only lasts 17 seconds, and meanwhile, there goes your wizard) As my friends always call those spells, Minor Taunt, Lesser Taunt, Taunt, Greater Taunt, Superios Taunt, Word of Taunt, and Full Taunt. Learn how to use them to your advantage, because, sometimes you want to agro. Example, You call an evac (only pullers or the cleric should call evacs) and your druid/wizzy is getting beat on, simple solution, heal them through the nose. Suddenly, you've got his mobs, and you can hold them better then their un armored selves as they port you out. Remember, Divine Aura only saves your butt, and if that's all your trying to save, you should think twice about playing the group cleric. Div aura stops your heals, and, if any party members are left, they will be expecting heals while you can't give them. So remember, taunting can be a good thing, and don't over use your aura in groups.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
