	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 22nd 12:48 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings,<br><br>Having the foolish notion in my Clerical head that saving EVERYONE in my party is part of my job, I occasionally find myself in the position of having to save their butts.<br><br>I can say, without a doubt, that a Cleric can save a party from almost any fate assuming a few things that are critical...<br><br>1) The party MUST listen to the Cleric and do as he or she says. Absolutely MUST. Nothing is more frustrating to a Cleric than to make a sacrifice just to have it accomplish nothing because the party ignored them.<br><br>2) As a Cleric, you have to be willing to lay down your life for your party if that is the only option.<br><br>If you have both of these going for you, here's how you can be the hero of the day.<br><br>1) Mem the AE Taunt, err... AE Heal Word of Health and whichever Divine spells you fancy.<br><br>2) Cast WoH 2 or 3 times. You should now have everythings direct attention, so tell your party to run.<br><br>3) Cast Divine as soon as you can, but NOT before your party starts to run. The reason being is that the Divine spells seem to be an ANTI-taunt, and you will immediately start losing mobs attentions.<br><br>Using this method I have stopped a train of over 30 mobs (mostly red and yellow cons) cold in it's tracks. The problem tho is the game engine will only allow a certain amount of mobs to target you. Because of this, your party NEEDs to be high- tailing it out of there so that by the time the target cycling is over the mobs that are now unable to hold you as a target will not switch to your party members. Even with that many trying their best to kill me, I still had enough time to cast the first divine spell (by then I had gone from full health to 2 bubbles!) and start following the party out, albeit making sure not to catch them. I got about half way to zone before dying, but my entire party got out totally unharmed as did a bunch of people standing at the zone.<br><br>So, just remember. A Cleric can save the party in more ways than one, and those divine spells may only effect yourself when you cast them... but can be used for so much more.<br><br>Balamur Stoutfaith<br>38th Circle Cleric<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
