	   <tr><td colspan=2>VERY well said.&nbsp;&nbsp;You have hit my playing style to the letter.  I understand about the agro factor and how many clerics complain about getting stomped on by a mob.  Well I for one don't mind agro'ing a mob if another caster (enchanter preferred) can mez or stun it away from the tank(s).  This takes some of the damage off the tank and allows you to save the mana if you're low.  <br><br>Clerics are designed to be semi-tanks so we can and usually do take a licking and keep on ticking.  &lt;g&gt;  I've been with several parties that don't understand that I CAN take a beating and still cast heals when needed.  I'm usually the reason the enchanter can mez a mob as I will stand my ground and let it beat away at me.  Most warriors will attempt to engage the mob but this ruins the mez effect because most are so used to swinging and not thinking there are others in the party with significant skills to offer during combat.<br>Lastly, we clerics still have the proverbial "ace in the hole" called Divine Aura.  If things get really stupid, it's less than a second to cast and you can haul butt or wait and most mobs will leave you be once they see they cannot hurt you anymore.  I know this spell well as it has saved my butt more times than I care to count.  <br>So I echo your sentiments about clerics and if played right, a cleric is one of the most enjoyable characters to play in this game.<br><br>Cya on Erollisi Marr,<br>GreyWolffe SilverStarr<br>25th Season Cleric<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
