	   <tr><td colspan=2>You are right about Complete Heal being the most mana-efficient.&nbsp;&nbsp;But I have come to hate it, even when I have a nice fat warrior with 3400 hp to use it on, and here's why:<br><br>Even with my Specialization in Alteration (heal) maxed, it takes about eight and a half seconds to cast CH.  More than once, I have begun casting, only to have things go bad.  A mob breaks mez or aggros from a side hallway and comes flying in most unexpectedly and starts beating on someone.  Usually that someone is the enchanter, who will die long before I finish the CH and recycle to get even a fast Remedy cast on him.  Or the someone is the tank; I've planned it so he gets his CH at 15 to 20% health, but his HP starts to plummet and he dies before the CH goes off.<br><br>Don't get me wrong: I still use it.  It's just that I hate it.<br><br>By the way, I have similar observations about our nuke.  It's probably mana-efficient to nuke a mob if it's pretty likely to take full damage from it.  Problem is, the nuke takes over six seconds to cast, and several more to recover from.  Meanwhile, the enchanter died. <br>&nbsp;<br>Ismena, 65 Cleric<br>Forbydyn, Rogue<br>Alethea, Bard<br>Darcye, Wizard<br>Darcie, Ranger<br>Tihmm, Enchanter<br>Prexus<br>That's =Doctor= Barbie to you</td></tr>
