	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96660728617247><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=96660728617247>Should I play a Cleric?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=96660728617247#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 10:01 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you are deciding whether to play a cleric, you need to understand your role in EQ.&nbsp;&nbsp;You will never be able to deal mass damage (although at 29 and 44+ you can do some DD, this is not the meat of your class).  You will never do damage in combat (if you melee with the best weapons available, you will never any appreciable damage to any mob that gives experience beyond 20th level).<br><br>What you can do as a cleric is control every fight you are in.  Clerics make the best group leaders in the game.  This is principally because they spend there EQ life medding, looking at health bars and following the flow of the combat.  Clerics also get good crowd control.  You have decent armor so you can take damage when needed (and lots of times when you would rather not).  You also have Divine Auroura - one of the best "get out of jail free" cards in the game.<br><br>Generally, your primary job will be to buff and to heal.  I always ask everyone in the group their hp after buffing - this allows me to know how many hp they have in each bar and what healing spells to have ready.<br><br>You should also be ready to Park mobs on bad pulls.  You do this by getting a mob on you away from the group (superior heal achieves this task very well).  You then cast stun to give yourself a few seconds to cast and cast root on the mob.  You then go back to the fight.  If root breaks, repeat - stun and root are very inexpensive spells and you will be able to control the extra mob until the group is ready to deal with it.  <br><br>You also have several different stun spells available to you.  Don't look at each new stun as an upgrade, but more as an additional opportunity to stop mobs from casting.  I frequently have 3 stuns ready if I think we will face casters.  Nothing speeds a fight like Stun, Stun, Stun, repeat.  Casting mobs frequently have fewer hp so one or two rounds of stuns (very mana efficient) will usually be enough for an entire fight.  <br><br>You also have 2 lines of fear spells - targetable and AoE.  Fear is wonderful if grouped with any class that can snare.  This allows fear kiting and is one of the most efficient ways to kill difficult mobs.  Just have the mob snared and cast fear - instant back shots for everyone.  It also helps in areas where mobs don't assist (not many places, but it can still help).  When facing multiple mobs, fear one that will not bring friends and he will run at top speed away.  Time the fear - when it breaks, you have about that much time before the mob will return so you know when to look for him.  Wave of fear is the Evac spell for clerics.  If you have an evacer, you wave of fear and give them time to cast.  If you don't have an evacer, you give everyone a few seconds in which to run for zone.  Stay behind and use divine aura so you are invulnerable and the mobs should all agro you initially buying your team a few more seconds - then turn tail and run for zone (or gate if you can get it off).<br><br>Clerics are difficult to play well, and often boring as well in that all you seem to do is stand - heal - sit.  But if the above sounds like your style of play - if you never want to be the damage dealer but like to be the target of all the mob attention, maybe a cleric is the class for you.<br><br>Baguette Ovenfresh<br>Cleric of the 45th Season<br>Quellious<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
