	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 19th 7:38 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Excellent advice Baguette -even if your name is a bit silly =).&nbsp;&nbsp;The AE Fear spell is probably the most underused assets a cleric has.  If you are in a situation where you know there is a good possibility of needing an evac a smart cleric will have this one memmed.  Believe me, the group will be giving you big pats on the back (and hopefully beer) when you use this to buy your druid or wizard enough time to save everyone's life.  Just remember, that your AE Fear spell has a pretty small radius so be sure to do one of the following: Get close to your evac'er if he's getting hit or wade into the center of the melee to be sure the mobs will be feared.  Ideally in this situation you'll be sitting next to the druid anyhow, keeping prepared for this possibility.<br><br>-Rook Sledgefist<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
