	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree, the AE Fear spell would be useful in this situation. And in all honesty I hadn't considered that.<br><br>I'm more familiar with Stunning and taunt pulling to allow time for evac. My normal routine is to stun the 1 annoying fast hitter that's on the evac caster (it never fails that there's one mob like this) and then to cast an AE Heal from the center of the party. And you thought Superior Healing was a taunt? Give THAT bad boy a try, everything comes running.<br><br>It's a good way to get yourself killed though, so you have to time it right, know how long the evac cast takes, etc. Otherwise you end up with every mob nearby pounding on you, and you cannot divine or the evac won't work on you.<br><br>I'll have to give wave of fear a try, I've never used it (for what it's worth, I jokingly refer to the Fear line of spells, such as Invoke Fear... as "Invoke Train").<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
